xolo_Adams\"}, {\"begin\": 265, \"end\": 270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999589963418, \"rank\": 4.100352971175723e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luxolo_Adams\", \"score\": 0.9999999998044586, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Luxolo Adams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luxolo_Adams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luxolo_Adams\"}, {\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999589963418, \"rank\": 4.100352971175723e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture,Gayton McKenzie, has used some of his super fan budget to fundLuxolo Adams'strip to theParis Olympics 2024.\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 554, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Adams, who will turn 28 on 1 August, was overlooked for the Team South Africa athletics squad for this year's Games in France.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Team South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999764677343, \"rank\": 2.343231119795015e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adams was one oftwocasualties afterWayde van Niekerksensationally optedoutof the 400m to focus on the 200m event instead, as reported byThe South African website.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fellow sprinterSinesipho Dambile, 22, also missed out on selection.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dambile has, however, been included as a reserve.\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Niekerk's decision meant there was no place for Adams in theTeam SAsquad - even though he has run a faster qualifying time in the half-lap event than Van Niekerk.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team SA has sent a34-personstrong athletics squad in Paris, of which23are men and11women.\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.092881460615391e-35, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1189, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999589963418, \"rank\": 4.100352971175723e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shaun Maswangani, Benjamin Richardson and Van Niekerk are the three runners in the men's 200m, the heats of which will take place on 5 August with the final scheduled for 8 August.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.8893515800486712, \"rank\": 0.12437498218171839, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 1254, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999925626071, \"rank\": 7.435079800150342e-09, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"None of the trio are expected to reach the final, let alone challenge for a medal.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gayton McKenzie spoke of having 'no jurisdiction regarding who should be included in the team, but that he did not want to break the spirit of a young man who is an inspiration to many in his village'.\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gayton_McKenzie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gayton McKenzie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gayton_McKenzie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gayton_McKenzie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adams hails from Burgersdorp in the Eastern Cape.\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1713, \"end\": 1724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgersdorp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Burgersdorp\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgersdorp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgersdorp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kyle Blignaut (shot put), Edmund du Plessis (800m), Elroy Galant (marathon), Victor Hogan (discus), Gardeo Isaacs (4x400m), Cheswill Johnson (long jump), Shaun Maswangani (100m, 200m, 4x100m), Stephen Mokoka (marathon), Ryan Mphalele (1 500m), Zakithi Nene (400m, 4x400m), Bradley Nkoana (4x100m), Antonie Nortje (4x400m), Lyth